# ScoreFlow Cursor Rules

## Workflow
1. Work in ONE phase at a time. Never jump between phases.
2. Always read BUILD_SPEC.md before starting a new file.
3. Stop and ask for confirmation before moving to the next phase.
4. Commit after each working sub-feature. Don't batch huge commits.
5. When unsure, ask before proceeding.

## Code quality
- TypeScript strict mode only. No `any` types.
- All API routes must validate inputs with Zod.
- All forms use react-hook-form + zod resolver.
- Use shadcn/ui components. Don't rewrite existing UI primitives.
- All client components must be marked 'use client' explicitly.
- Tailwind utility classes only. No CSS modules or inline styles.

## Multi-tenancy invariants (NEVER violate)
- Every table except `users`, `agencies`, `subscription_plans` has `agency_id` column.
- Every database query from an authenticated user must filter by `agency_id`.
- Never trust client-supplied `agencyId` or `businessId` — always derive from session.
- Subdomain determines tenant; don't trust request body to determine tenant.
- Platform admin users: `agency_id IS NULL`, `role = 'platform_admin'`.
- All other users: `agency_id IS NOT NULL`.
- Never query across agencies in one request (except as platform admin).

## Security
- Supabase service role key NEVER exposed to client.
- All tables must have RLS enabled before they're used.
- POS access tokens encrypted at rest.
- Stripe webhooks must verify signature.
- Rate limit all public endpoints and auth endpoints.

## When adding a new feature
1. Update the Drizzle schema first.
2. Generate + run migration.
3. Write RLS policies for any new table.
4. Build the API route with Zod validation.
5. Build the UI last.

## File conventions
- Route groups use parentheses: `(marketing)`, `(agency)`, etc.
- Server components by default; client components only when interactivity needed.
- API routes colocated under `src/app/api/`.
- Database queries live in `src/lib/db/queries/` (not in components).
- Shared types in `src/types/`.

## Anti-patterns to avoid
- ❌ Direct Supabase queries from client components (use API routes or Server Actions).
- ❌ Hardcoded agency IDs or business IDs.
- ❌ Skipping RLS "temporarily for dev."
- ❌ Using `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.
- ❌ Storing secrets in NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables.
- ❌ Building multiple phases at once.
